# ai-memory hero GIF — single source of truth.
#
# Render:   vhs docs/assets/demo/demo.tape         (from repo root)
#     or:   npm run demo:render
# Output:   docs/assets/demo/demo.gif
#
# Story (≈30s, deliberately tight):
#   1. comment line       — name what ai-memory does upstream (extract)
#   2. layout listing     — show the team-aware per-author folders
#   3. cat one decision   — show what a typed memory looks like
#   4. rules --agents-md  — convert the whole store into AGENTS.md
#   5. head AGENTS.md     — show the artifact every AI editor reads
#   6. outro line         — name where it gets reused
#
# `extract` is intentionally NOT a live command in this GIF. Running extract
# inside vhs's headless terminal would require an LLM key in the render
# environment and a working source detector — fragile, and the artifact
# view is what actually moves the viewer (typed memory → AGENTS.md). The
# README around the GIF and docs/assets/demo/RECORDING.md cover what
# extract does upstream.
#
# Maintainer notes:
# - .ai-memory/ under scenario/ is hand-curated, not extracted live.
# - scenario/AGENTS.md is generated by frame 4; .gitignore-d so re-renders
#   stay deterministic. The setup block deletes it before recording.
# - Commands are POSIX-only (cat, ls, grep, rm, head). Render on
#   macOS / Linux / WSL / Docker. See RECORDING.md.

Output docs/assets/demo/demo.gif

Set FontSize 14
Set Width 1180
Set Height 720
Set Theme "Dracula"
Set Padding 28
Set TypingSpeed 35ms
Set PlaybackSpeed 1.0

# ---------- hidden setup ----------
Hide
Type "cd docs/assets/demo/scenario"
Enter
Type "rm -f AGENTS.md"
Enter
Type "clear"
Enter
Show
# ---------- /hidden setup ----------

# Frame 1 — the framing line (≈3s)
Sleep 600ms
Type "# Extract typed decisions/conventions from your editor's chat history."
Enter
Sleep 1s

# Frame 2 — show the per-author memory layout (≈4s)
Type "ls -1R .ai-memory | grep '\.md$'"
Enter
Sleep 2.5s

# Frame 3 — open one extracted decision (≈8s; viewer needs time to read)
Type "cat .ai-memory/conor/decisions/2026-04-22-adopt-oauth-pkce.md"
Enter
Sleep 5.5s

# Frame 4 — turn the whole store into AGENTS.md (≈5s)
Type "ai-memory rules --target agents-md --all-authors"
Enter
Sleep 3s

# Frame 5 — show the artifact every AI editor reads (≈5s)
Type "head -25 AGENTS.md"
Enter
Sleep 4.5s

# Outro — name the downstream consumers (≈4s)
Type "# Cursor, Claude Code, Windsurf and Copilot Chat all read AGENTS.md."
Enter
Sleep 1.8s
